# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# Build output
ui/dist/
web/dist/assets/

.todo

# Runtime files
brok.log
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
*.db.key

# JWT signing secret — generated by the API server on first start when no
# BROKOLI_JWT_SECRET env var is set. The file lands wherever the server's
# CWD happens to be (repo root in dev, api/ in `go test ./api/...`), so we
# match it anywhere in the tree without anchoring. Never commit; never
# include in release artifacts. Goreleaser refuses to publish a release
# with this file untracked because it dirties the working tree.
.brokoli-jwt-secret

# Node modules
node_modules/